### Define Playwright Page Object Model for Search Functionality

Source: https://github.com/microsoft/playwright/blob/main/docs/src/pom.md

This code defines a Playwright Page Object Model (`SearchPage`) to encapsulate interactions with a search page. It includes methods for navigating to the search page and performing a search. The constructor initializes the Playwright `Page` object and locates the search input field.

```java
package models;

import com.microsoft.playwright.*;

public class SearchPage {
  private final Page page;
  private final Locator searchTermInput;

  public SearchPage(Page page) {
    this.page = page;
    this.searchTermInput = page.locator("[aria-label='Enter your search term']");
  }

  public void navigate() {
    page.navigate("https://bing.com");
  }

  public void search(String text) {
    searchTermInput.fill(text);
    searchTermInput.press("Enter");
  }
}
```

