### Access Playwright Frame Objects by Name or URL

Source: https://github.com/microsoft/playwright/blob/main/docs/src/frames.md

This example shows how to retrieve a specific frame object from a page using its name attribute or URL pattern. Once the frame object is obtained, it can be used to interact with elements directly within that frame, such as filling an input field. This approach is useful for more complex frame interactions or when the frame's content needs to be manipulated more extensively.

```js
// Get frame using the frame's name attribute
const frame = page.frame('frame-login');

// Get frame using frame's URL
const frame = page.frame({ url: /.*domain.*/ });

// Interact with the frame
await frame.fill('#username-input', 'John');
```

```java
// Get frame using the frame"s name attribute
Frame frame = page.frame("frame-login");

// Get frame using frame"s URL
Frame frame = page.frameByUrl(Pattern.compile(".*domain.*"));

// Interact with the frame
frame.fill("#username-input", "John");
```

